{
  "info": {
    "name": "Register Ricardian Forest v3.0 - 8 CALLS (WRITE + WRITE 1.5 PDF + PDF + UPLOAD CADES + WRITE 2 CADES + UPLOAD CADES CLIENT + WRITE 3 CLIENT COUNTERSIGN + VERIFY)",
    "_postman_id": "bbbbbbbb-1111-2222-3333-cccccccccccc",
    "description": "Aggiornato per Ricardian v3.0 con CONTROFIRMA CLIENTE (firma annidata .p7m.p7m). Flusso completo: 1) WRITE registra il Ricardian on-chain (richiede l'oggetto 'subscriber' per l'art. 8-ter c.2 L. 12/2019). 4) UPLOAD CADES carica e verifica il .p7m del firmatario. 5) WRITE 2 CADES registra on-chain la firma del firmatario. 5b) UPLOAD CADES CLIENT carica il .p7m.p7m del cliente (firma annidata sopra il p7m del firmatario): il server fa doppia estrazione, verifica che il p7m interno coincida con la firma del firmatario gia' registrata e che il PDF annidato coincida con la baseline. 5c) WRITE 3 CLIENT COUNTERSIGN registra on-chain la controfirma cliente in uno slot separato (prerequisito: WRITE 2 CADES gia' eseguito). 6) VERIFY ora esegue la DOPPIA verifica on-chain (firma firmatario + controfirma cliente). Compila {{subscriberLegalEntity}}, {{subscriberIdentifier}}, {{subscriberMethod}} prima del flusso.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1) WRITE (All-in-one) -> sets {{forestUnitId}} {{merkleRoot}} {{ricardianHash}} {{storageUri}} {{txHash}}",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{API_URL}}/api/contract/write",
          "host": ["{{API_URL}}"],
          "path": ["api", "contract", "write"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"forestUnitId\": \"{{forestUnitId}}\",\n  \"useIPFS\": false,\n  \"subscriber\": {\n    \"legalEntity\": \"{{subscriberLegalEntity}}\",\n    \"identifier\": \"{{subscriberIdentifier}}\",\n    \"method\": \"{{subscriberMethod}}\"\n  }\n}"
        }
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "// Pre-flight check: avvisa se le variabili subscriber non sono compilate",
              "const le = pm.collectionVariables.get('subscriberLegalEntity');",
              "const id = pm.collectionVariables.get('subscriberIdentifier');",
              "if (!le || !id) {",
              "  console.warn('[!] subscriberLegalEntity o subscriberIdentifier non compilati. La WRITE fallirà con errore 400.');",
              "  console.warn('[!] Compila le variabili di collection prima di eseguire la chiamata.');",
              "}"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "if (!j || j.ok !== true) {",
              "  console.log('WRITE failed response:', j);",
              "  if (j && j.hint) console.log('Hint:', j.hint);",
              "  if (j && j.example) console.log('Example body:', JSON.stringify(j.example, null, 2));",
              "}",
              "if (j && j.forestUnitId) pm.collectionVariables.set('forestUnitId', j.forestUnitId);",
              "if (j && j.merkleRoot) pm.collectionVariables.set('merkleRoot', j.merkleRoot);",
              "if (j && j.ricardianHash) pm.collectionVariables.set('ricardianHash', j.ricardianHash);",
              "if (j && j.ricardianUri) pm.collectionVariables.set('storageUri', j.ricardianUri);",
              "if (j && j.onchain && j.onchain.txHash) pm.collectionVariables.set('txHash', j.onchain.txHash);",
              "if (j && j.onchain && j.onchain.blockNumber !== undefined) pm.collectionVariables.set('blockNumber', String(j.onchain.blockNumber));"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1.5) WRITE PDF ONLY -> sets {{forestUnitId}} {{merkleRoot}} {{ricardianHash}} {{txHash}} {{pdfViewUrl}} {{pdfDownloadUrl}}",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{API_URL}}/api/contract/write-1.5-pdf",
          "host": ["{{API_URL}}"],
          "path": ["api", "contract", "write-1.5-pdf"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"forestUnitId\": \"{{forestUnitId}}\"\n}"
        }
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const j = pm.response.json();",
              "if (!j || j.ok !== true) {",
              "  console.log('WRITE 1.5 PDF failed response:', j);",
              "}",
              "if (j && j.forestUnitId) pm.collectionVariables.set('forestUnitId', j.forestUnitId);",
              "if (j && j.merkleRoot) pm.collectionVariables.set('merkleRoot', j.merkleRoot);",
              "if (j && j.ricardianHash) pm.collectionVariables.set('ricardianHash', j.ricardianHash);",
              "if (j && j.onchain && j.onchain.txHash) pm.collectionVariables.set('txHash', j.onchain.txHash);",
              "if (j && j.onchain && j.onchain.blockNumber !== undefined) pm.collectionVariables.set('blockNumber', String(j.onchain.blockNumber));",
              "if (j && j.pdf && j.pdf.viewUrl) pm.collectionVariables.set('pdfViewUrl', j.pdf.viewUrl);",
              "if (j && j.pdf && j.pdf.downloadUrl) pm.collectionVariables.set('pdfDownloadUrl', j.pdf.downloadUrl);"
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2) View Ricardian PDF -> uses {{forestUnitId}}",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{API_URL}}/api/ricardian/pdf/{{forestUnitId}}/view",
          "host": ["{{API_URL}}"],
          "path": ["api", "ricardian", "pdf", "{{forestUnitId}}", "view"]
        }
      }
